### **Transitions Explained**

| Transition               | Meaning                                                           |
| ------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Î´(qâ‚€, a, Zâ‚€) = (qâ‚€, aZâ‚€) | If reading `a` and stack top is `Zâ‚€`, push `a`                    |
| Î´(qâ‚€, a, a) = (qâ‚€, aa)   | If reading another `a`, push one more `a` on top                  |
| Î´(qâ‚€, b, a) = (qâ‚, Îµ)    | On seeing first `b`, pop one `a` (switch to popping mode, qâ‚)     |
